SIMPLE: shame
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shame
<hw>Shame</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>shame</ets>,
<ets>schame</ets>, AS. <ets>scamu</ets>, <ets>sceamu</ets>; akin to OS.
& OHG. <ets>scama</ets>, G. <ets>scham</ets>, Icel.
<ets>sk⟦oum⟧mm</ets>, <ets>shkamm</ets>, Sw. & Dan. <ets>skam</ets>, D.
& G. <ets>schande</ets>, Goth. <ets>skanda</ets> shame, <ets>skaman
sik</ets> to be ashamed; perhaps from a root <ets>skam</ets> meaning to
cover, and akin to the root (<ets>kam</ets>) of G. <ets>hemd</ets>
shirt, E. <ets>chemise</ets>. Cf. <er>Sham</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A painful sensation excited by a consciousness of guilt or
impropriety, or of having done something which injures reputation, or of
the exposure of that which nature or modesty prompts us to
conceal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>HIde, for <qex>shame</qex>,⟦br⟧
Romans, your grandsires' images,⟦br⟧
That blush at their degenerate progeny.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Have you no modesty, no maiden <qex>shame</qex>?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Reproach incurred or suffered; dishonor; ignominy;
derision; contempt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ye have borne the <qex>shame</qex> of the heathen.</q>
<rj><qau>Ezek. xxxvi. 6.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Honor and <qex>shame</qex> from no condition rise.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And every woe a tear can claim⟦br⟧
Except an erring sister's <qex>shame</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The cause or reason of shame; that which brings
reproach, and degrades a person in the estimation of others;
disgrace.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O C<?/sar, what a wounding <qex>shame</qex> is this!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Guides who are the <qex>shame</qex> of religion.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The parts which modesty requires to be covered; the
private parts.</def> <rj><au>Isa. xlvii. 3.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>For shame!</b></col> <cd>you should be ashamed; shame on
you!</cd> -- <col><b>To put to shame</b></col>, <cd>to cause to feel
shame; to humiliate; to disgrace.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧Let them be driven
backward and <xex>put to shame</xex> that wish me evil.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Ps. xl. 14.</au></rj> </cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shame</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Shame
<hw>Shame</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Shamed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Shaming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make ashamed; to
excite in (a person) a comsciousness of guilt or impropriety, or of
conduct derogatory to reputation; to put to shame.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Were there but one righteous in the world, he would . . .
<qex>shame</qex> the world, and not the world him.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To cover with reproach or ignominy; to dishonor; to
disgrace.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And with foul cowardice his carcass <qex>shame</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To mock at; to deride.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ye have <qex>shamed</qex> the counsel of the poor.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. xiv. 6.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shame</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Shame
<hw>Shame</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>scamian</ets>,
<ets>sceamian</ets>. See <er>Shame</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>To be
ashamed; to feel shame.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I do <qex>shame</qex>⟦br⟧
To think of what a noble strain you are.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shamefaced</ent>⟦br⟧
